<p>For the latest installment of the occasional <a href="https://dailynous.com/tag/academic-equipment/">academic equipment</a> series, let&#8217;s talk coffee.<span id="more-54785"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-54786 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/gaggia-orione-espresso-machine.png" alt="" width="747" height="500" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/gaggia-orione-espresso-machine.png 1655w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/gaggia-orione-espresso-machine-300x201.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/gaggia-orione-espresso-machine-1024x686.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/gaggia-orione-espresso-machine-768x514.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/gaggia-orione-espresso-machine-1536x1028.png 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/gaggia-orione-espresso-machine-400x268.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 747px) 100vw, 747px" /></p>
<p>How is coffee done in your department? Is it every-coffee-drinker-for-themselves? Is there a communal coffee-making device of some sort?</p>
<p>If there is an office coffee machine, what is it? What do you (realistically) wish it was? Why? Who pays for the coffee? Which coffee do you use (and who gets to decide)? Who cleans and maintains the machines?</p>
<p>That is: what is your department&#8217;s coffee practice? What would a good departmental coffee practice be? Should there even be a communal coffee machine? And what about the tea drinkers?</p>
<p>If it is every-coffee-drinker-for-themselves in your department, do you bring your own&#8212;and if so, in what?&#8212;or do you actually brew your own in your office&#8212;and if so, how?</p>
<p>For what it&#8217;s worth, our department recently acquired a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Keurig-K-Elite-Temperature-Capability-Programmable/dp/B078NN17K3?crid=1ZSRLW5H3L7HX&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.YOUgHe8cOqLaT2rU_46c_8vl1YrW-Th9JQWR9LMQ4hCY00rf9Uj-7OYis1Emniq-aAo8421PCg6p5P3zKEAHpcvQteF_9v9eBkUKmwTL61GxUfGYivUhSZ0pM0KtCvYQOzqo78Yg_GiDF7pMYgZxorZHsg3Fr4c0evNaVeB7EOd0RM-Ax6mBkSNhATsSnXRgy7rlqEV7tMe1FjZlcun6bbZRHhaqgMtPwmHYGREAYHtWiyYwYUCEDDNJEb5nLaNj9fqgPzPMSJpyfWfORoTqlSmdheRj6U_-CS9AcV1XAVM.zmH07bC88Y0w4w_vnODT0lUfVjLEQdsqWc0BP1ezvzg&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Keurig&amp;qid=1756310712&amp;sprefix=keurig%2Caps%2C100&amp;sr=8-1&amp;ufe=app_do%3Aamzn1.fos.9fe8cbfa-bf43-43d1-a707-3f4e65a4b666&amp;th=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dainou-20&amp;linkId=3246ecce1cbec54fb7f03876fd533de3&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Keurig</a> machine, and people who want to use it provide their own pods (like <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Caribou-Coffee-Daybreak-Morning-Single-Serve/dp/B00474VPLI?crid=2Q3CTPYQADUUG&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.toAzpW8KGMALRp94i5b1Y9_GXnKN_LkekGCmJSJdtP8lIl_1KvPPR3rP65419os7HN7whqSj5NAS72kXsa1yPc3TNmCnxj-YP7_PUAVP3IMnUMEDyP0aJoRKKOGn0i0lD9-BwfCBbsBCkLP-35DlUPZHvm4nkLQ6qIaa2i08WjFuvCYHipI3hzuSyLi4A4aysD9tlextJaAHirXrgwJ8aeod9OwNmpvm1SPtcvZjk3-65zKecK2ux3DJR2MrBMiuUz4g0jj-Hb50N4Tw7bv1oXSp6UQCTuPr2trxvYSGcb4.SVY6wLMbBCEkmWNYm4YrIGT9C_B3XhUxhIDB7mh6-0M&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Keurig%2Bcoffee%2Bpods%2Bcaribou%2Bdaybreak&amp;qid=1756311005&amp;sprefix=keurig%2Bcoffee%2Bpods%2Bcaribou%2Bdaybreak%2Caps%2C104&amp;sr=8-6&amp;th=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dainou-20&amp;linkId=0d711773f936455d63b55ab9554444af&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">these</a>). I, however, am still in the habit of bringing my own coffee in <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Fellow-12-Carter-Slide-Mug/dp/B0F3LL8THQ?crid=3MTBCAS35YX8O&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.XIMwfhWVkkQEm4lJDSVRBJNtKvOCOUgYbiNsWqzGRmkkZSEsC80oKLy5ev_zpJ